modules.description: Provides functions to compute the factorial of a non-negative integer, check if a number is prime, and generate a list of Fibonacci numbers up to a specified limit. Operates on integers and lists of integers. Used to perform mathematical validations and sequence generation in algorithmic implementations.

The module provides a foundation for handling optional values through a set of core operations. It includes a type for representing absence or presence of a value and supports chaining, mapping, and filtering operations. Users can safely compose functions that may fail or return undefined results. Examples include transforming optional inputs, combining multiple optional values, and extracting values with default fallbacks.
